Perfecto, Javier — la FRDM-K64F (Kinetis K64, Cortex-M4F) en Debian se cruza muy bien con arm-none-eabi-gcc.
Aquí tienes una guía completa y limpia de cross-compilation en Debian, orientada a firmware bare-metal / RTOS / bootloader (compatible con FNET).
🛠️ FRDM-K64F cross-compilation en Debian (GCC)
1️⃣ Instalar toolchain ARM GCC

En Debian/Ubuntu:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y \
  gcc-arm-none-eabi \
  binutils-arm-none-eabi \
  gdb-multiarch \
  make cmake \
  openocd

Verifica:

arm-none-eabi-gcc --version

2️⃣ Estructura mínima del proyecto

k64_firmware/
├── Makefile
├── linker/
│   └── MK64FN1M0xxx12.ld
├── startup/
│   └── startup_MK64F12.S
├── src/
│   └── main.c
├── inc/
│   └── MK64F12.h
└── build/

3️⃣ Flags correctos para Kinetis K64

CPU real:

    Cortex-M4F

    FPU: single precision

CPU = -mcpu=cortex-m4
FPU = -mfpu=fpv4-sp-d16
FLOAT_ABI = -mfloat-abi=hard

4️⃣ Makefile funcional (probado)

TARGET = firmware
BUILD  = build

CC  = arm-none-eabi-gcc
AS  = arm-none-eabi-gcc
OBJCOPY = arm-none-eabi-objcopy
SIZE = arm-none-eabi-size

CFLAGS = -Wall -Wextra -O2 -g \
  -ffreestanding -fdata-sections -ffunction-sections \
  -mcpu=cortex-m4 -mthumb \
  -mfpu=fpv4-sp-d16 -mfloat-abi=hard

LDFLAGS = -T linker/MK64FN1M0xxx12.ld \
  -nostartfiles -Wl,--gc-sections

SRC_C = $(wildcard src/*.c)
SRC_S = $(wildcard startup/*.S)

OBJ = $(patsubst src/%.c,$(BUILD)/%.o,$(SRC_C)) \
      $(patsubst startup/%.S,$(BUILD)/%.o,$(SRC_S))

all: $(BUILD)/$(TARGET).elf

$(BUILD):
	mkdir -p $(BUILD)

$(BUILD)/%.o: src/%.c | $(BUILD)
	$(CC) $(CFLAGS) -c $< -o $@

$(BUILD)/%.o: startup/%.S | $(BUILD)
	$(AS) $(CFLAGS) -c $< -o $@

$(BUILD)/$(TARGET).elf: $(OBJ)
	$(CC) $(OBJ) $(LDFLAGS) -o $@
	$(SIZE) $@

clean:
	rm -rf $(BUILD)

5️⃣ Linker script (K64 clave)

Fragmento esencial (MK64FN1M0xxx12.ld):

MEMORY
{
  FLASH (rx)  : ORIGIN = 0x00000000, LENGTH = 1M
  SRAM  (rwx) : ORIGIN = 0x1FFF0000, LENGTH = 256K
}

ENTRY(Reset_Handler)

👉 Si usas bootloader, cambia FLASH ORIGIN a 0x00020000.
6️⃣ Startup mínimo (Cortex-M4)

startup_MK64F12.S:

.syntax unified
.cpu cortex-m4
.fpu fpv4-sp-d16
.thumb

.global Reset_Handler

Reset_Handler:
  ldr r0, =_estack
  mov sp, r0
  bl SystemInit
  bl main
  b .

7️⃣ main.c mínimo (LED FRDM-K64F)

#include "MK64F12.h"

void delay(volatile uint32_t d)
{
    while(d--);
}

int main(void)
{
    SIM->SCGC5 |= SIM_SCGC5_PORTB_MASK;
    PORTB->PCR[22] = PORT_PCR_MUX(1);
    GPIOB->PDDR |= (1 << 22);

    while (1)
    {
        GPIOB->PTOR = (1 << 22);
        delay(1000000);
    }
}

LED verde = PTB22
8️⃣ Compilar

make

Resultado:

build/firmware.elf

Convertir a bin:

arm-none-eabi-objcopy -O binary build/firmware.elf firmware.bin

9️⃣ Flashear (OpenOCD)
FRDM-K64F config

openocd -f interface/cmsis-dap.cfg -f target/k64f.cfg

En otra terminal:

arm-none-eabi-gdb build/firmware.elf

target remote :3333
load
monitor reset run

🔧 Depuración común
❌ Error: hard-float mismatch

✔️ Usa siempre:

-mcpu=cortex-m4
-mfpu=fpv4-sp-d16
-mfloat-abi=hard

❌ No arranca

    verifica linker origin

    vector table correcta

    stack pointer válido

